win11-window-tiling
==================

Windows 11-style automatic window tiling for Debian.

Features
--------

- Snap windows to halves, quarters, and custom zones
- Snap Assist: suggests other windows when snapping (GNOME Tiling Shell)
- Drag-to-edge snapping (GNOME, KDE KZones)
- Windows 11 keyboard shortcuts: Super + Arrow keys
- Auto-detects GNOME, KDE Plasma, or falls back to X11

Installation
------------

  sudo dpkg -i win11-window-tiling_1.0.0_all.deb
  sudo apt install -f   # resolve any missing dependencies

Setup
-----

  win11-tiling-setup

Log out and back in after setup.

Desktop Support
---------------

GNOME (Debian 12+)
  Installs Tiling Shell extension with Snap Assistant and Fancy Zones.
  https://github.com/domferr/tilingshell

KDE Plasma 6
  Installs KZones KWin script for zone-based snapping.
  https://github.com/gerritdevriese/kzones

X11 (XFCE, MATE, etc.)
  Uses wmctrl + xbindkeys for Super+Arrow hotkeys.

Commands
--------

  win11-tiling-setup          Enable tiling for your desktop
  win11-tiling-setup --status Show configuration status
  win11-tile left             Manually snap active window left
  win11-tiling-setup --uninstall  Remove user config

Keyboard Shortcuts
------------------

  Super + Left        Snap to left half
  Super + Right       Snap to right half
  Super + Up          Maximize
  Super + Down        Restore / minimize
  Super + Shift + Arrows   Quarter snapping (X11/KDE)

